We were INDEED kids so desperate trying to be grown…this was the OG artwork I made for SOS. Me and my friends in 5th grade thinking we were so bad ass. Luckily I think I hit my “bad” phase early, so by the time I got to high school It was out of my system.  We would steal our parent’s cigarettes and take the beach bus down Topanga Canyon, then ride our skateboards all the way down to the Venice boardwalk. And yes it is where I saw my first pair of real life tideez. 🤗From the Marlboro Reds and the Swisher Sweets, to the riding 100 miles an hour down the 101 freeway at 3am standing in the back of Marcus’s Silverado. Everything I wrote in Summer Of Santeria is from my own true coming of age story and I’m glad I got to share it with y’all! 
Question? Who else used to smoke cigarettes in the mall stairwell and then go to “The body Shop” and spray yourself with every perfume tester they had and then when your moms picked u up and asked why you wreaked of 10 different colognes you just told them you got into a freak cologne fight? Anyone else? Just me? 

#summerofsanteria #comingofage #thevalley

I must admit, I’ve always been embarrassed expressing my BIG dreams and aspirations. Even as a kid. Nobody even knew I sang until like senior year of H.S. I was too embarrassed to tell people that every night I dreamt of singing to thousands of people. Even admitting them to myself makes me feel this pit in my stomach, like this doom and dread “WHAT IF YOU FAIL!!?” and then you look like a fool because you told everyone. And it feels just as nerve racking when you think “WHAT IF I SUCCEED?” It seems counterintuitive but that evokes the same feeling of dread. What if I get everything I want!? TERRIFYING. It’s taken me a really long time to process that weird fear of both failing and succeeding. And I feel I’m JUST beginning that journey (big ups to my therapist!) I realize that even though up to this point I’ve acted in SPITE of that fear which has gotten me this far, I need to start THINKING and BELIEVING differently in order to reach the next level.  I want to headline the Hollywood Bowl in September of 2026. and if you’re not coming, helping me get there or cheering me on, literally GO away from me DEMON! Who’s coming? 

#hollywoodbowl #2026 #prettysister #singers #livemusic
